  "history": {
    "en": "Traditional Colombian scent hound descended from European and North American scenthounds brought to Colombia, adapted over centuries to local terrain and climate. Developed by rural hunters for tenacity and scenting skills from local and Spanish scent hounds. Officially recognized in Colombia in early 2000s and received provisional FCI recognition in 2014.",
    "zh": "传统的哥伦比亚嗅觉猎犬，源自欧洲和北美嗅觉猎犬引入哥伦比亚后，经数世纪适应当地地形和气候。由乡村猎人从本地和西班牙嗅觉猎犬中培育，以坚韧和嗅觉技能著称。2000年代初在哥伦比亚正式获认可，2014年获FCI临时承认。"
  },
